    </section>

    <section class="section2">
    <h2>Ingredients</h2> 
    <ul>
      <li>- 1 recipe pastry for a 9 inch double crust pie</li>
      <li>- 1/2 cup unsalted butter</li>
      <li>- 3 tablespoons all-purpose flour</li>
      <li>- 1/4 cup water</li>
      <li>- 3 tablespoons all-purpose flour</li>
      <li>- 1/4 cup water</li>
      <li>- 1/2 cup white sugar</li>
      <li>- 1/2 cup packed brown sugar</li>
      <li>- 8 Granny Smith apples - peeled, cored and sliced</li> 
    </ul>
    </section>
        <img class='cooking-info' src="/img/cooking-info.png">

              <hr></hr>
    <section class="section3">
    <h2>Directions</h2> 
    <ol>
      <li>1) Preheat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Melt the butter in a saucepan. Stir in flour to form a paste. Add water, white sugar and brown sugar, and bring
    to a boil. Reduce temperature and let simmer.</li>
      <li>2)Place the bottom crust in your pan. Fill with apples, mounded slightly. Cover with a lattice work crust. Gently pour the sugar and butter liquid over the crust. Pour slowly so
    that it does not run off.</li>
      <li>3) Bake 15 minutes in the preheated oven. Reduce the temperature to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Continue baking for 35 to 45 minutes, until apples are soft.</li>  
    </ol>
    </section>